	(text "The analog pins on an Arduino Micro \n(or any Arduino) can be used as digital inputs \nfor a button matrix. \nWhile these pins are designed for analog input, \nthey can also function as standard digital I/O pins. \nYou would connect the button matrix to these analog \npins just as you would to digital pins, \nand read their states using digitalRead(). "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 232.918 87.376 0)
